%N A396384 Decimal expansion of the constant D = Sum_{n>=0} 1/(2*n! + 1).
%C A396384 D arises in three independent contexts:
%C A396384 (1) Game theory: expected number of green-slot outcomes in a hierarchical roulette where wheel n has 2*(n-1)! red/black slots and 1 green slot.
%C A396384 (2) Cryptography: expected number of honeypot triggers in a cascading cipher where level n has 2*(n-1)! real keys and 1 decoy key.
%C A396384 (3) Biology: expected number of premature stop-codon reading events. In all three cases D < 1 is the stability threshold.
%F A396384 Equals Sum_{n>=1} n/(2*n!+n).
%F A396384 Equals e/2 - Sum_{n>=0} 1/(2*n!*(2*n!+1)).
%e A396384 D = 1/3 + 1/3 + 1/5 + 1/13 + 1/49 + ... = 0.96895437342956...
%t A396384 N[Sum[1/(2*(n-1)! + 1), {n, 1, Infinity}], 50]
%o A396384 (Python)
%o A396384 from mpmath import mp, nsum, factorial, inf
%o A396384 mp.dps = 50
%o A396384 print(nsum(lambda n: 1/(2*factorial(n-1)+1), [1, inf]))
%o A396384 (PARI) suminf(k = 1, 1/(2*(k-1)!+1)) \\ _Amiram Eldar_, May 24 2026
%Y A396384 Cf. A001113 (decimal expansion of e), A000142 (factorials), A372392.
